        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 14
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> the nightwing of the Star Tower (G7) — sent by <strong>Zon-Kuthon himself</strong> weeks after the curse woke, to ward the Chamber of the Well until a new curate takes the post; bound by the god's will, <em>not</em> the curse (he can never become an anchor). He greets visitors telepathically, invisible above the well: <strong>give him a curate, and the way below opens</strong> — a new curate (or a banishment-grade effect) is his only release from the post. He prefers a volunteer, ideally a Kuthite — <em>Sial or Laori are perfect</em> — otherwise he nominates the most Zon-Kuthon-like PC. Refused outright, his patience snaps: he attacks to force someone to beg acquiescence. <strong>See the G-H page for the Devil-You-Know turn this triggers</strong> — and for what he reveals once a curate is settled (Zon-Kuthon <em>wants</em> Kazavon's fragment cut out of the queen).</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
